A member of the COVID-19 government response team (L) asks questions to a resident during a door to door COVID-19 coronavirus screening in Westdene, Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - There's been an increase in local COVID-19 cases. South Africa has recorded 19 COVID-19 related deaths, bringing the total to 238. The total number of cases now stands at 12,739. READ: COVID-19 death toll rises to 219 Health Minister Zweli Mkhize said there are 5,676 recoveries. More than 403,000 tests have been conducted so far. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.